# K-HARDEN-8: Cursor cold-start entry (legacy .cursorrules format).
#
# Modern Cursor reads `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` (see 000-agents-alignment.mdc);
# this file is the fallback for older Cursor versions.
#
# Start here: read AGENTS.md — the canonical cross-agent contract. It defines
# the full read order (§2), risk classes (§5), restricted surfaces (§6), the
# PR-only workflow (§14a), the audit doctrine (§9), the obligation ledger (§16),
# and the Karpathy coding principles (§13). This file does not restate them.
#
# Cursor obeys that one contract identically to every other platform, free to
# use its own native strengths to realize it — the Layer 1 / Layer 2 model in
# AGENTS.md §2.
#
# AGENTS.md is canonical. If anything here conflicts, AGENTS.md wins.
